Hezbollah security agents, as well as Lebanese troops, were trying to cordon off the area to keep the angry crowds away from the blast site. 

Ali Oleik, an accountant who works in a nearby office building, said: ‘Suddenly the whole area went bright and we started running away.

‘I saw two bodies on the street, one of a woman and another of a man on a motorcycle who was totally deformed.’

